reverse crowned barrel.  This simply means that the barrel has been re-cut with a slight stant inward toward the barel (typically 11%).  By fllush cutting the barrel, you lower the chance of the barrel catching anything in addition to improving accuracy and the asthetic of the gun.  As shown in the pictures, the gun has Wilson Combat Cocobolo Starburst grips.  The original hard carrying case is included as well as the cases contents which include a holster, 2 full size magazines, a magazine holster for two magazines, and all documentation and paperwork.  This gun has been well maintianed but has not yet even been fired, excepte test rounds perhaps.  I have plenty more pictures as well and I'm happy to answer any questions.  I'm also happy to meet to let anyone take a look at the gun in person.  It really is a must see.  The original cost was roughly $1,100 and I've invested another $350 for the trigger job and the work that was done on the barrel (IE flush cut and reverse crowned).  I have a host of spare Wilson Combat parts that will also be included as extras as I no longer have any need for them.  These included a spare trigger, sear spring, and I'll throw in a spare bull barrel by Storm Lake (also flush cut and reverse crowned), a spare full length guide rod, a reverse plug with barrel support and a spare recoil spring.  The cost of these items was at least $300 plus a $200 fee to have the bull barrel reverse crowned and flush cut.  Don't miss this opportunity to add a high qualit 1911 to your collection at less than half of the total investment that - Backup sights integral in the long top Picatinny rail. Tritium insert in front sight post.
- Simple field stripping for easy maintenance.
- Uses standard AR-15/M16/STANAG magazines.

title: For Sale:  Are you looking for a great price on a shotgun??  Take a look...
postcontent: I am an FFL Dealer who works out of my home and carry no inventory.  And because I don't carry any inventory,  I can generally save you money compared to the big box sporting goods stores.  If you are looking for a particular firearm; email, text, or call me with what you are looking for with the manufacturer, MODEL NUMBER, caliber, and even a UPC or ITEM NUMBER from the manufacturer website and I will quote you a out the door price that includes the gun, shipping, markup, background check and sales tax.  In otherwords, this is all you would pay.  I also have a full time professional career and do this on the side so if I don't get back to you immediately just keep that in mind but generally I can answer you in a short time and ALWAYS on the same day.  So, with that in mind, I look forward to working with you, and helping you with all of your firearm needs. First step is if you agree to the price that I give you is to give me the go ahead to order the firearm that you want.  NO DOWN PAYMENT IS REQUIRED!!  I accept cash, check, money orders and can now do credit cards!  (Additional 2% added to total bill for credit card orders)  Once your firearm comes in generally within 2-5 business days in most cases, you come to complete the background check and pay for your firearm.  Background checks are done right away which means as long as you pass you get to leave with your firearm right away!  Thanks for looking and hope to help you with all of your firearms and ammunition needs!   Chad  Days End Firearm Sales Marshfield,  WI. 54449 REDACTED  REDACTED

title: For Sale:  Used Glock 17 Gen 3 w/ Polished Barrel, 3.5lb connector, 15lb recoil spring, steel guide rod.
postcontent: Hey there. I'm looking to sell my Glock 17 Gen 3 with some small little aftermarket features included. Looking for cash only, no trades. CCW holders preferred.  Meet locally. Price is firm.
